summary: An ordinance accepting deeds from G.W. Lincoln and Emma Lincoln, his wife, and G.L. Shultz; Emma J. Mooney, a widow; V.P. Lobdell and Margeret K. Lobdell, his wife; James R. Gates and Helen F. Gates, husband and wife; George H. Hall and Clara M. Hall, his wife, and Pearl S. Rushong; Hannah Lindroth; Edwin A. Winfield and Bertha Winfield, his wife; Tillie A. Diebold, a widow; and Charles W. Weedin and Catharine A. Weedin, his wife; to the City of Seattle and laying off Oswego Place.
